HEADWORD: Forestay
<hw>Fore"stay`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A large, strong rope, reaching from the foremast head to the
bowsprit, to support the mast. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Ship</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>forested</ent>⟦br⟧
